The following examples use the `listingsAndReviews` collection in the
`sample_airbnb` database. If you have the [sample data sets](available-sample-datasets) on your cluster, you can create a custom
MongoDB Search index for [geo](bson-data-types-geo) type and run the
example queries on your cluster. The [index builder](fts-tutorial-ref) contains
instructions for loading the [sample data sets](available-sample-datasets), creating an [index definitions](ref-index-definitions), and running MongoDB Search queries.

The following is a sample index definition for
indexing the `address.location` field in the `listingsAndReviews`
collection:

```json
{
  "mappings": {
    "fields": {
      "address": {
        "fields": {
          "location": {
            "indexShapes": true,
            "type": "geo"
          }
        },
        "type": "document"
      },
      "property_type": {
        "type": "token"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

The following example uses the `geoShape` operator to search for
properties that have nothing in common with the specified longitude and
latitude coordinates in Hawaii.

The query includes a:

- [$limit](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/limit) stage to limit the output to `3` results.

- [$project](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/project) stage
  to exclude all fields except `name` and `address`.

**Input:**

```json
db.listingsAndReviews.aggregate([
  {
    "$search": {
      "geoShape": {
        "relation": "disjoint",
        "geometry": {
          "type": "Polygon",
          "coordinates": [[[-161.323242,22.512557],
                          [-152.446289,22.065278],
                          [-156.09375,17.811456],
                          [-161.323242,22.512557]]]
        },
        "path": "address.location"
      }
    }
  },
  {
    $limit: 3
  },
  {
    $project: {
      "_id": 0,
      "name": 1,
      "address": 1,
      score: { $meta: "searchScore" }
    }
  }
])
```

